    • stopIsShiftable

      public boolean stopIsShiftable(Stop stop, int dir)
      Returns whether a stop's order is shiftable up or down. A stop's order cannot be shifted up or down if it's already at the end of the stop list, and a pickup cannot be shifted after a delivery and vice versa.
      Parameters:
      stop - The stop to be checked.
      dir - The direction of the shift (up (-1) or down (+1)).
      Returns:
      Whether the stop is shiftable in the given direction.

    • stopComputingTour

      public boolean stopComputingTour()
      Stops the thread computing the tour, is only effective if tsp has returned an intermediary result (in which case, that result will become effective). Otherwise, the thread is not interrupted yet.
      Returns:
      Whether the thread has indeed been interrupted or not.

      public void processTSPUpdate(TSP tsp)
      Processes a TSP result (algorithm giving an intermediary or final result) by populating tourPaths with the appropriate Paths from the stopsGraph and setting the stop's times / order of passage.
      Parameters:
      tsp - The TSP instance holding the result

    • update

      public void update(Observable o, UpdateType updateType)
      Called when the TSP instance notifies TourData that an intermediary result has been found. If the computing thread is still going, processes that intermediary result and notifies the view (otherwise it's no use, the view has already been notified of the final result in stopComputingTour())
      Specified by:
      update in interface Observer
      Parameters:
      o - The observable object who notified the view.
      updateType - The type of update that has been made.
